# Page Accessibility Mindset

## Core Principle

**Before telling users to "check the page" or "access the link", always verify there's an actual UI element to navigate there.**

## Required Checks

When creating or modifying pages/routes:

1. **Is there a navigation element?**
   - Link in navbar/sidebar/menu
   - Button that routes to this page
   - Card/item that links here
   - Breadcrumb trail

2. **Can users discover it naturally?**
   - Not just `/hidden-admin-panel` in URL bar
   - Accessible through normal app flow
   - Visible in the UI

3. **Create navigation as part of the feature**
   - Don't leave pages orphaned
   - Add menu items, buttons, or links
   - Update layouts/navigation components

## Bad vs Good Approaches

### ❌ BAD

```
Agent: "I've created the Trip History page. You can access it at /trip-history"
```

**Problem**: No navigation element exists. User has to manually type URL.

### ✅ GOOD

```
Agent: "I've created the Trip History page and added a navigation link in the main menu. 
Users can now access it by clicking 'Trip History' in the navigation bar."
```

**What was done**:
- Created the page/route
- Added `<Link>` in navigation component
- Verified the flow works end-to-end

## Implementation Pattern

When adding a new page:

```vue
<!-- 1. Create the page: resources/js/pages/TripHistory.vue -->
<template>
  <div>Trip History Content</div>
</template>

<!-- 2. Add navigation in layout or menu component -->
<template>
  <nav>
    <Link :href="index.url()">Dashboard</Link>
    <Link :href="tripHistory.url()">Trip History</Link> <!-- NEW -->
  </nav>
</template>
```

## Questions to Ask Yourself

Before finalizing any page/route work:

- [ ] Where will users click to reach this page?
- [ ] Is there a visible link/button in the UI?
- [ ] Have I tested the full navigation flow?
- [ ] Or is this an API/backend-only route that doesn't need UI access?

## Exception

Backend API routes, webhooks, or admin-only programmatic endpoints don't need UI navigation. But **user-facing pages always need accessible navigation**.

---

**Remember**: Users navigate through UI elements, not URL bars. Always create the navigation path.